THOUGHT
The user wants me to fix an LLVM miscompilation in the `instcombine` pass.
The issue is that `select (icmp ne X, 0), (icmp samesign eq X, C), false` is incorrectly transformed to `icmp samesign eq X, C`. This transformation is incorrect when `X` is 0 and `C` is a negative constant. In this case, the `select` evaluates to `false`, but the `icmp samesign eq` evaluates to `poison`.

The problematic code is in `llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp`. I need to find the code that performs this transformation and add a check to prevent it when the `icmp` has the `samesign` attribute.

The relevant code snippet looks like this:
```cpp
// select (icmp ne X, 0), (icmp eq X, C), false -> icmp eq X, C
// where C is non-zero.
if (auto *ICI = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(Cond))
  if (ICI->getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE &&
      match(ICI->getOperand(1), m_Zero())) {
    Value *X = ICI->getOperand(0);
    if (auto *TCmp = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(TVal))
      if (TCmp->getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ &&
          TCmp->getOperand(0) == X && match(FVal, m_False())) {
        if (const auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(TCmp->getOperand(1)))
          if (!C->isNullValue())
            return TCmp;
      }
  }
```
This code needs to be modified to check for the `samesign` attribute on `TCmp`. The simplest and safest fix is to disable the optimization if `samesign` is present. I can do this by adding `!TCmp->hasSameSign()` to the condition.

The modified condition will be:
`TCmp->getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ && !TCmp->hasSameSign() && TCmp->getOperand(0) == X && match(FVal, m_False())`

I will use `sed` to insert `!TCmp->hasSameSign() &&` into the correct line in `llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp`.

```bash
sed -i 's/\(TCmp->getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ &&\)/\1 !TCmp->hasSameSign() \&\&/' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp
```

